definitions.definition: An object, act or words believed to have magic power (usually carries a positive connotation).
( often in the plural ) The ability to persuade , delight or arouse admiration .
examples: She tried to win him over with her charms .

definitions.definition: A small trinket on a bracelet or chain, etc., traditionally supposed to confer luck upon the wearer.
examples: She wears a charm bracelet on her wrist.

definitions.definition: The collective noun for a group of goldfinches .
( particle physics ) A quantum number of hadrons determined by the number of charm quarks and antiquarks .
( finance ) A second-order measure of derivative price sensitivity, expressed as the instantaneous rate of change of delta with respect to time.
( graphical user interface , Microsoft Windows ) An icon providing quick access to a command or setting.
